Rule: If `education` is `Masters`, then the likelihood of earning more than $50k a year increases.
If `workclass` is `Self-Employed`, then the likelihood of earning more than $50k a year increases, even with a lower level of education like HS-grad.
If `education` is `Masters` and `workclass` is `Other/Unknown`, the individual is still likely to earn more than $50k a year.
If `education` is `HS-grad` and `workclass` is `Self-Employed`, the likelihood of earning more than $50k a year increases.
